genresAdvancedInfo.name: uk rockabilly
genresAdvancedInfo.description: UK rockabilly is a genre of music that emerged in the 1950s and combines elements of rock and roll with country and blues. It is characterized by its fast-paced rhythms, twangy guitars, and energetic performances. UK rockabilly has been popular in the UK for decades and has influenced many British musicians, including the Beatles and the Rolling Stones. Today, it continues to be a beloved genre among rockabilly enthusiasts around the world.
